---
import Site from '../../layouts/Site.astro';
---

<Site title="Casewell — the matter-centric AI legal assistant" description="Docketing, conflicts, drafting, time, and billing — run by AI, signed off by you, audited end to end.">
	<!-- Hero -->
	<section class="dark-band">
		<div class="wrap rise" style="padding-block: clamp(3.5rem, 8vw, 6rem); text-align: center;">
			<span class="kicker" style="color: #a5b4fc;">⚖️ Casewell</span>
			<h1 style="color: white; max-width: 40rem; margin-inline: auto;">
				The assistant that thinks in matters, not messages.
			</h1>
			<p class="lead" style="color: #a5b0c8; margin-top: 1.2rem; max-width: 36rem; margin-inline: auto;">
				Intake with conflict checks. Deadlines that docket themselves from conversation. Drafts
				from your clause library. Time captured as you mention it. Everything filed, cited, and
				audited on the matter.
			</p>
			<div style="display: flex; gap: 0.8rem; justify-content: center; margin-top: 2rem; flex-wrap: wrap;">
				<a class="btn" href="/pricing">See pricing</a>
				<a class="btn ghost on-dark" href="/docs/casewell/getting-started">Get started</a>
			</div>
			<p style="color: #8b95ad; margin-top: 1.4rem; font-size: 0.9rem;">
				Open source, MIT licensed, free to self-host —
				<a href="https://github.com/abrahamFerga/casewell" style="color: #a5b4fc;">github.com/abrahamFerga/casewell</a>
			</p>
		</div>
	</section>

	<!-- A day with it -->
	<section class="band">
		<div class="wrap">
			<span class="kicker">A Tuesday, with Casewell</span>
			<h2 style="max-width: 34rem;">Say it once. It's docketed, logged, and filed.</h2>
			<div class="grid cols-2" style="margin-top: 2.5rem;">
				{[
					['9:04', '“Run a conflict check on Meridian Holdings”', 'Checked against every recorded party across your matters — result reported, attestation hash-chained, before the matter opens.'],
					['9:12', '“Open the matter and prepare the engagement letter”', 'Matter created, parties recorded, the letter drafted from YOUR clauses, rendered to PDF, and held for your approval before filing.'],
					['11:40', '“The answer is due August 14”', 'Docketed with reminders at 7 days and 48 hours. Deadlines drive notifications — nothing lives in anyone’s memory.'],
					['14:25', '“Log half an hour on Vandelay — call with opposing counsel”', 'A billable time entry, captured in the moment it’s mentioned. Pre-bills export to PDF, filed on the matter for review.'],
					['16:50', '“Review this contract against our playbook”', 'Every rule checked, every finding cited to the file. New language flagged as new — never silently invented.'],
					['17:30', '“Brief me on where Meridian stands”', 'One look: parties, deadlines, tasks, hours, documents. The overview your morning coffee deserves.'],
				].map(([time, quote, result]) => (
					<div class="card">
						<div style="font-family: var(--mono); color: var(--brand); font-weight: 700; font-size: 0.85rem;">{time}</div>
						<h3 style="margin-top: 0.4rem;">{quote}</h3>
						<p style="margin-top: 0.4rem;">{result}</p>
					</div>
				))}
			</div>
		</div>
	</section>

	<!-- Guardrails -->
	<section class="band" style="background: var(--surface); border-block: 1px solid var(--line);">
		<div class="wrap" style="display: grid; gap: 3rem; grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(19rem, 1fr)); align-items: center;">
			<div>
				<span class="kicker">Built for a profession with rules</span>
				<h2>Leverage, not liability.</h2>
				<p class="lead" style="margin-top: 1rem;">
					Every draft is a starting template for attorney review. The assistant never invents
					statutes or citations, flags language outside your library, and recommends licensed
					review — by design, in its instructions, on every matter.
				</p>
			</div>
			<div class="grid" style="gap: 0.9rem;">
				{[
					['🧱', 'Ethical walls', 'A restricted matter vanishes from every tool, tab, and search for everyone outside the wall.'],
					['🛡', 'Approval-gated writes', 'Filing, closing, sending — held for a human. Time capture is the one deliberate exception.'],
					['📜', 'Tamper-evident attestations', 'Conflict-check attestations are hash-chained; the record shows if anyone touched it.'],
					['👥', 'Roles your admin shapes', 'Paralegal, associate, partner — permission baselines are yours to edit, per workspace.'],
				].map(([emoji, title, text]) => (
					<div style="display: flex; gap: 0.9rem; border: 1px solid var(--line); border-radius: 12px; padding: 1rem 1.2rem; background: var(--bg); box-shadow: var(--shadow-1);">
						<span style="font-size: 1.25rem;">{emoji}</span>
						<div>
							<h3 style="font-size: 0.98rem;">{title}</h3>
							<p style="color: var(--muted); font-size: 0.9rem;">{text}</p>
						</div>
					</div>
				))}
			</div>
		</div>
	</section>

	<!-- Channels + composition -->
	<section class="band">
		<div class="wrap">
			<div class="grid cols-3">
				<div class="card">
					<div class="icon">💬</div>
					<h3>Clients where they already are</h3>
					<p>Intake over WhatsApp: clients message like they always do; documents and details land on the matter, conflict-checked.</p>
				</div>
				<div class="card">
					<div class="icon">🧩</div>
					<h3>Specialists on demand</h3>
					<p>Switch to the drafting agent or the docketing clerk per conversation — each sees only its own tools. Chain them as workflows.</p>
				</div>
				<div class="card">
					<div class="icon">📚</div>
					<h3>Your knowledge, cited</h3>
					<p>Index a matter's documents and ask questions with quoted, cited answers — walls and permissions enforced inside search too.</p>
				</div>
			</div>
		</div>
	</section>

	<!-- CTA -->
	<section class="band dark-band">
		<div class="wrap" style="text-align: center;">
			<h2 style="max-width: 32rem; margin-inline: auto;">Open your first matter today.</h2>
			<p class="lead" style="color: #a5b0c8; margin-top: 1rem;">Solo, Team, or your own dedicated cloud — live the moment you subscribe.</p>
			<div style="display: flex; gap: 0.8rem; justify-content: center; margin-top: 2rem; flex-wrap: wrap;">
				<a class="btn" href="/pricing">Choose a plan</a>
				<a class="btn ghost on-dark" href="/docs/casewell/getting-started">Read the docs</a>
			</div>
		</div>
	</section>
</Site>
